#{115}{}{I, uh, will be back soon.}
{115}{}{一、 呃，很快就回来。 -- I, uh, will be back soon.}
#{116}{}{My name is Ricardo Bertolini - I'm the owner of this place, and this is my apartment. Usually I do not accept clients... Unless they have a business proposal for me.}
{116}{}{我叫里卡多・贝托里尼――我是这个地方的主人，这是我的公寓。通常我不接受客户。。。除非他们有我的商业计划书。 -- My name is Ricardo Bertolini - I'm the owner of this place, and this is my apartment. Usually I do not accept clients... Unless they have a business proposal for me.}
#{117}{}{Word on the streets is that you were seen with that old ranch fellow - Oliver. If that's the path you choose, I won't stop you. But - if that's the case - from now on there will be no business relations between us. If you want to keep working for me - prove that you're still trustworthy.}
{117}{}{街上有消息说有人看见你和那个农场的老家伙奥利弗在一起。如果你选择这条路，我不会阻止你。但是――如果是这样的话――从现在起，我们之间就没有业务关系了。如果你想继续为我工作-证明你仍然值得信赖。 -- Word on the streets is that you were seen with that old ranch fellow - Oliver. If that's the path you choose, I won't stop you. But - if that's the case - from now on there will be no business relations between us. If you want to keep working for me - prove that you're still trustworthy.}
#{118}{}{It's just a deceptive maneuver. I will prove my worth}
{118}{}{这只是个骗人的策略。我要证明我的价值 -- It's just a deceptive maneuver. I will prove my worth}
#{119}{}{Is it so unpleasant that I talk with your competitor? That's understandable.}
{119}{}{我和你们的竞争对手谈话是不是很不愉快？这是可以理解的。 -- Is it so unpleasant that I talk with your competitor? That's understandable.}
#{120}{}{I have a proposal. We could arrange a mutually beneficial deal, regarding the sale of Nuka-Cola... }
{120}{}{我有个建议。我们可以就努卡可乐的销售安排一个互利的交易。。。 -- I have a proposal. We could arrange a mutually beneficial deal, regarding the sale of Nuka-Cola... }
#{121}{}{The offer is tempting, but my bar only serves alcohol drinks. No one will buy Cola here. If we were some sort of a cafe, I would probably agree.}
{121}{}{这个提议很诱人，但我的酒吧只供应酒精饮料。没有人会在这里买可乐。如果我们是咖啡馆，我可能会同意。 -- The offer is tempting, but my bar only serves alcohol drinks. No one will buy Cola here. If we were some sort of a cafe, I would probably agree.}
#{122}{}{Ah, got it.}
{122}{}{啊，明白了。 -- Ah, got it.}
#{123}{}{Boss, I know a lady who's forced to pay her debts to the casino after the death of her husband. Could you help to resolve this issue?}
{123}{}{头儿，我认识一位女士，她丈夫死后，她被迫向赌场还债。你能帮忙解决这个问题吗？ -- Boss, I know a lady who's forced to pay her debts to the casino after the death of her husband. Could you help to resolve this issue?}
#{124}{}{I've heard this story... Mrs. Clover, correct? As a courtesy to you, I am willing to forgive these debts - moreover, the total sum is not much for this casino. Inform the administrator about my wish.}
{124}{}{我听过这个故事。。。克洛弗太太，对吗？出于对你的礼貌，我愿意免除这些债务――而且，这家赌场的总金额不多。告诉管理员我的愿望。 -- I've heard this story... Mrs. Clover, correct? As a courtesy to you, I am willing to forgive these debts - moreover, the total sum is not much for this casino. Inform the administrator about my wish.}
#{125}{}{Thank you, Mr. Bertolini!}
{125}{}{谢谢你，伯托里尼先生！ -- Thank you, Mr. Bertolini!}
#{130}{}{I heard rumors that you've offended Mr. Thompson. What can you say about this?}
{130}{}{我听说你冒犯了汤普森先生。你能说些什么？ -- I heard rumors that you've offended Mr. Thompson. What can you say about this?}
#{131}{}{He was asking for it!}
{131}{}{他是自找的！ -- He was asking for it!}
#{132}{}{I'm not going to make excuses. The matter is between him and me only.}
{132}{}{我不会找借口的。这件事只在他和我之间。 -- I'm not going to make excuses. The matter is between him and me only.}
