#{201}{}{Oh, that's how it is... I'll try.}
{201}{}{哦，就是这样。。。我试试看。 -- Oh, that's how it is... I'll try.}
#{202}{}{Oliver and I used to get along well, but ten years ago a conflict emerged. When civil war broke out in the town, we stood on opposite sides of the barricades. Now, when those, who at the helm, are completely different people, I want to put an end to this story. You will help me. Here's something to instill your confidence - your payment.}
{202}{}{奥利弗和我过去相处得很好，但十年前发生了冲突。当镇上爆发内战时，我们站在路障的对面。现在，当那些掌舵的人是完全不同的人时，我想结束这个故事。你会帮助我的。这里有一些东西可以灌输你的信心-你的报酬。 -- Oliver and I used to get along well, but ten years ago a conflict emerged. When civil war broke out in the town, we stood on opposite sides of the barricades. Now, when those, who at the helm, are completely different people, I want to put an end to this story. You will help me. Here's something to instill your confidence - your payment.}
#{203}{}{Can you tell me a little more about this story?}
{203}{}{你能再给我讲讲这个故事吗？ -- Can you tell me a little more about this story?}
#{204}{}{I'm in.}
{204}{}{我加入了。 -- I'm in.}
#{205}{}{I'll return when the job's done.}
{205}{}{工作完成后我会回来的。 -- I'll return when the job's done.}
#{206}{}{Perhaps... It will help you to better navigate the situation. In this case, I will be able to answer some questions.}
{206}{}{也许。。。它将帮助你更好地驾驭形势。在这种情况下，我将能够回答一些问题。 -- Perhaps... It will help you to better navigate the situation. In this case, I will be able to answer some questions.}
#{207}{}{I need to know about that civil war.}
{207}{}{我要知道那场内战。 -- I need to know about that civil war.}
#{208}{}{Why did you end up on different sides?}
{208}{}{你为什么会站在不同的一边？ -- Why did you end up on different sides?}
#{209}{}{What prevents you from making peace and becoming partners?}
{209}{}{是什么阻止你和别人和好，成为伴侣？ -- What prevents you from making peace and becoming partners?}
#{210}{}{Do you wish for... Luciano's death?}
{210}{}{你希望。。。卢西亚诺的死？ -- Do you wish for... Luciano's death?}
#{211}{}{May I ask another question?}
{211}{}{我可以再问一个问题吗？ -- May I ask another question?}
#{212}{}{It happened around six years ago. Local businessmen couldn't get along because of the division in spheres of influence. Competing in conditions of increased population and lack of resources led many to ruin: poverty in homes, gangsters on the streets, sabotage within enterprises. Then the clans began to kill each other. All of this stopped when the "big daddy" of the wasteland came with his crew, as they told "to carry out some order", and ended up outsmarting everyone here with his own hidden agenda. Since then, the town had no rest.}
{212}{}{这事发生在六年前。由于势力范围的分裂，当地商人无法相处。在人口增长和资源匮乏的条件下竞争导致许多人破产：家中贫穷、街头流氓、企业内部破坏。然后，氏族开始互相残杀。当荒原上的“大老爹”带着他的船员来到这里时，这一切都停止了，因为他们告诉“执行一些命令”，最后以他自己隐藏的议程胜过了这里的每个人。从那以后，镇上再也没有休息过。 -- It happened around six years ago. Local businessmen couldn't get along because of the division in spheres of influence. Competing in conditions of increased population and lack of resources led many to ruin: poverty in homes, gangsters on the streets, sabotage within enterprises. Then the clans began to kill each other. All of this stopped when the "big daddy" of the wasteland came with his crew, as they told "to carry out some order", and ended up outsmarting everyone here with his own hidden agenda. Since then, the town had no rest.}
#{213}{}{It's a long conversation. Let's just say we have different views on how the town should develop. I like the ideas offered by Mr. Thompson. Oliver's opinions are radically opposite.}
{213}{}{这是一次很长的谈话。就说我们对这个城镇应该如何发展有不同的看法。我喜欢汤普森先生提出的想法。奥利弗的观点截然相反。 -- It's a long conversation. Let's just say we have different views on how the town should develop. I like the ideas offered by Mr. Thompson. Oliver's opinions are radically opposite.}
#{214}{}{Good question. Probably the overall situation in the town, and... How should I put it... This old man's stubbornness. I can not dissuade Oliver from his ideas, but they directly contradict my ideas on this town's future.}
{214}{}{问得好。可能是镇上的整体情况，还有。。。我该怎么说。。。这个老人的固执。我无法劝阻奥利弗放弃他的想法，但这些想法直接与我对这个城市未来的看法相矛盾。 -- Good question. Probably the overall situation in the town, and... How should I put it... This old man's stubbornness. I can not dissuade Oliver from his ideas, but they directly contradict my ideas on this town's future.}
#{215}{}{No way! The death of this man would only ruin his ranch. It would lose workers, slaves, and its resources would be stolen. I have other thoughts on his account, but it's still too early for you to be aware of them.}
{215}{}{不可能！这个人的死只会毁了他的农场。它将失去工人、奴隶，其资源也将被偷。我对他还有其他想法，但你现在还不知道。 -- No way! The death of this man would only ruin his ranch. It would lose workers, slaves, and its resources would be stolen. I have other thoughts on his account, but it's still too early for you to be aware of them.}
#{216}{}{Occasionally, Luciano ships food to the the Silver Legacy's restaurant. I need you to undermine his reputation when he'll do it next time. Go to the restaurant, wait for the convoy and sabotage the deal. How you'll do it - I don't know and don't want to know. But it must be done so that it looked like a an oversight from Luciano's men.}
{216}{}{偶尔，卢西亚诺会把食物送到银遗产餐厅。我需要你在他下次这么做的时候破坏他的名声。去餐厅，等车队来破坏交易。你会怎么做-我不知道也不想知道。但必须这样做，让它看起来像是卢西亚诺手下的疏忽。 -- Occasionally, Luciano ships food to the the Silver Legacy's restaurant. I need you to undermine his reputation when he'll do it next time. Go to the restaurant, wait for the convoy and sabotage the deal. How you'll do it - I don't know and don't want to know. But it must be done so that it looked like a an oversight from Luciano's men.}
#{217}{}{I'm on my way.}
{217}{}{我在路上。 -- I'm on my way.}
#{218}{}{Can I learn more about the situation that has caused tension with Luciano?}
{218}{}{我能进一步了解导致与卢西亚诺关系紧张的情况吗？ -- Can I learn more about the situation that has caused tension with Luciano?}
#{219}{}{Did you manage do what I asked?}
{219}{}{你按我说的做了吗？ -- Did you manage do what I asked?}
#{220}{}{I'm still working on it.}
{220}{}{我还在努力。 -- I'm still working on it.}
#{221}{}{Mission accomplished, Luciano's reputation was undermined.}
{221}{}{任务完成后，卢西亚诺的声誉受到了损害。 -- Mission accomplished, Luciano's reputation was undermined.}
#{222}{}{This is good news. Did you do it... Quietly as I asked?}
{222}{}{这是个好消息。是你做的。。。像我说的那样安静？ -- This is good news. Did you do it... Quietly as I asked?}
#{223}{}{Thank you, Mr. Bertolini. Will there be any new jobs?}
{223}{}{谢谢你，伯托里尼先生。会有新工作吗？ -- Thank you, Mr. Bertolini. Will there be any new jobs?}
#{224}{}{I have just been informed that Oliver Luciano has passed away. This defeats the purpose of my plan, and concerning your service... Well, I have no further orders for you. You may leave.}
{224}{}{我刚刚得知奥利弗・卢西亚诺已经去世了。这违背了我计划的目的，关于你的服务。。。好吧，我没有更多的订单给你。你可以走了。 -- I have just been informed that Oliver Luciano has passed away. This defeats the purpose of my plan, and concerning your service... Well, I have no further orders for you. You may leave.}
#{225}{}{Oh, Oliver, why did you let me down... }
{225}{}{哦，奥利弗，你为什么让我失望。。。 -- Oh, Oliver, why did you let me down... }
#{226}{}{Yes, you've proven yourself, so I can trust you with a more serious mission. Your payment will also correspond with the significance of each task.}
{226}{}{是的，你已经证明了你自己，所以我可以相信你有一个更严肃的任务。你的报酬也将与每项任务的重要性相一致。 -- Yes, you've proven yourself, so I can trust you with a more serious mission. Your payment will also correspond with the significance of each task.}
#{227}{}{What do I need to do?}
{227}{}{我需要做什么？ -- What do I need to do?}
#{228}{}{I need you to destroy Luciano's enterprise. He has to be knocked out of the rut, so that later I could dictate my conditions to him. And Oliver should not die under any circumstances.}
{228}{}{我需要你摧毁卢西亚诺的事业。他必须被淘汰出局，这样以后我才能把我的条件告诉他。奥利弗在任何情况下都不应该死。 -- I need you to destroy Luciano's enterprise. He has to be knocked out of the rut, so that later I could dictate my conditions to him. And Oliver should not die under any circumstances.}
#{229}{}{To destroy his whole enterprise? How should I do it?!}
{229}{}{毁掉他的整个事业？我该怎么做？！ -- To destroy his whole enterprise? How should I do it?!}
#{230}{}{The objective is accepted. Wait for the results, Mr. Bertolini.}
{230}{}{目标被接受。等待结果，贝托里尼先生。 -- The objective is accepted. Wait for the results, Mr. Bertolini.}
#{231}{}{Who's paying who, for gecko's sake?! This is *your* headache, so you should decide, what to do. But, if I were you, I'd first studied closely the central facilities of the ranch - the hangar, brahmin corral or paddock with slaves. The more losses you arrange, the better.}
{231}{}{谁付钱给谁，看在壁虎的份上？！这是你的头痛，所以你应该决定怎么办。但是，如果我是你，我首先会仔细研究牧场的中心设施――机库、婆罗门畜栏或有奴隶的围场。你安排的损失越多越好。 -- Who's paying who, for gecko's sake?! This is *your* headache, so you should decide, what to do. But, if I were you, I'd first studied closely the central facilities of the ranch - the hangar, brahmin corral or paddock with slaves. The more losses you arrange, the better.}
#{232}{}{Maybe this is a risky question - but still - why is this necessary at all? After all, it provides the main Reno market with food... }
{232}{}{也许这是一个危险的问题-但仍然-为什么这是必要的？毕竟，它为雷诺的主要市场提供了食物。。。 -- Maybe this is a risky question - but still - why is this necessary at all? After all, it provides the main Reno market with food... }
#{233}{}{I'm not going to discuss my plans with you. But I will say that Luciano is not as simple as you think. This is no ordinary rancher, whose head is stuck in a brahmin's ass. And he is not some kind of trader, who sell the screw nuts to regressive savages. He is the driving force. One of the most powerful in the town today. People are rallying around him; he dictates his conditions, and he also has some sort of plan. Hmm... I don't know, maybe you're from one of those places where food is just another product. But, here and now, it's what the life in this desert is gathering around. Now, do you understand?}
{233}{}{我不打算和你讨论我的计划。但我要说，卢西亚诺并不像你想象的那么简单。这不是一个普通的农场主，他的头卡在一个婆罗门的屁股里，他也不是一个商人，他把螺帽卖给退化的野蛮人。他是驱动力。今天镇上最有权势的人之一。人们聚集在他周围；他决定他的条件，他也有某种计划。隐马尔可夫模型。。。我不知道，也许你来自那些食物只是另一种产品的地方。但是，此时此地，沙漠中的生命正聚集在这里。现在，你明白了吗？ -- I'm not going to discuss my plans with you. But I will say that Luciano is not as simple as you think. This is no ordinary rancher, whose head is stuck in a brahmin's ass. And he is not some kind of trader, who sell the screw nuts to regressive savages. He is the driving force. One of the most powerful in the town today. People are rallying around him; he dictates his conditions, and he also has some sort of plan. Hmm... I don't know, maybe you're from one of those places where food is just another product. But, here and now, it's what the life in this desert is gathering around. Now, do you understand?}
#{234}{}{What did you manage to accomplish?}
{234}{}{你成功地完成了什么？ -- What did you manage to accomplish?}
#{235}{}{Nothing right now, but I'll handle it later.}
{235}{}{现在没什么，但我以后再处理。 -- Nothing right now, but I'll handle it later.}
#{236}{}{I'm sorry, but completing the task without a violent resolution wasn't an option. Believe me, it was the only possible solution.}
{236}{}{我很抱歉，但是没有一个暴力的解决方案完成任务是不可能的。相信我，这是唯一可能的解决办法。 -- I'm sorry, but completing the task without a violent resolution wasn't an option. Believe me, it was the only possible solution.}
#{237}{}{Oh yes, just like you wanted. No one suspects anything.}
{237}{}{哦，是的，就像你想的那样。没人怀疑什么。 -- Oh yes, just like you wanted. No one suspects anything.}
#{238}{}{In this case, it's fair to cut your payment by half. You did only half of the job and broke our agreement. I appreciate your efforts, but am yet to close my eyes on this... Misunderstanding.}
{238}{}{在这种情况下，减半付款是公平的。你只做了一半的工作，违反了我们的协议。我很感激你的努力，但是我还没有闭上眼睛。。。误会。 -- In this case, it's fair to cut your payment by half. You did only half of the job and broke our agreement. I appreciate your efforts, but am yet to close my eyes on this... Misunderstanding.}
#{239}{}{I am pleased by your diligence - you truly adapt well.}
{239}{}{我为你的勤奋而高兴――你真的适应得很好。 -- I am pleased by your diligence - you truly adapt well.}
#{240}{}{My informants tell a different story. You're trying to fool me, and that's usually not forgivable. You are lucky I do not want to make a shooting spree in this operating casino, as it would harm its reputation. Now get out.}
{240}{}{我的线人讲了一个不同的故事。你想愚弄我，这通常是不可原谅的。你很幸运，我不想在这个经营赌场里大肆开枪，因为那样会损害它的声誉。现在出去。 -- My informants tell a different story. You're trying to fool me, and that's usually not forgivable. You are lucky I do not want to make a shooting spree in this operating casino, as it would harm its reputation. Now get out.}
#{241}{}{[Leave peacefully.]}
{241}{}{[平静地离开。] -- [Leave peacefully.]}
#{242}{}{In some ways we are alike - I don't forgive those who refuse to pay me for the work. Now you die!}
{242}{}{在某些方面我们是一样的-我不原谅那些拒绝付钱给我工作的人。现在你死定了！ -- In some ways we are alike - I don't forgive those who refuse to pay me for the work. Now you die!}
#{243}{}{[Head to the ranch.]}
{243}{}{[前往牧场] -- [Head to the ranch.]}
#{244}{}{I need your advice on how to do the job better. Can a murder solve the problem?}
{244}{}{我需要你关于如何把工作做得更好的建议。谋杀能解决问题吗？ -- I need your advice on how to do the job better. Can a murder solve the problem?}
#{245}{}{If you ever speak with such folly again, it will be our last conversation. I pay you for your own clever ideas... But, if you are really struggling with the job, then try to poison the supplies, or at least plant some explosives into them.}
{245}{}{如果你再这样胡说八道，那将是我们最后一次谈话了。我付钱给你是为了你自己的聪明想法。。。但是，如果你真的在为这份工作而挣扎，那就试着毒害这些物资，或者至少在里面放些炸药。 -- If you ever speak with such folly again, it will be our last conversation. I pay you for your own clever ideas... But, if you are really struggling with the job, then try to poison the supplies, or at least plant some explosives into them.}
#{246}{}{I thank you, Mr. Bertolini, You've helped me alot.}
{246}{}{谢谢你，伯托里尼先生，你帮了我很多。 -- I thank you, Mr. Bertolini, You've helped me alot.}
#{247}{}{Alright, I'll try.}
{247}{}{好吧，我试试。 -- Alright, I'll try.}
#{250}{}{Reception is over for now. Come back after eight in the morning.}
{250}{}{接待暂时结束。早上八点以后回来。 -- Reception is over for now. Come back after eight in the morning.}
#{251}{}{Thief! Guards! A thief!}
{251}{}{小偷！警卫！小偷！ -- Thief! Guards! A thief!}
#{252}{}{All of a *sudden* a fire broke out in the Luciano's food hangar, and a large part of the goods have been destroyed. }
{252}{}{突然间，卢西亚诺的食品库发生了火灾，大部分货物都被毁了。 -- All of a *sudden* a fire broke out in the Luciano's food hangar, and a large part of the goods have been destroyed. }
#{253}{}{The ranch had a *incidental* cattle plague, soon after my *coincidental* visit there. }
{253}{}{在我偶然造访农场后不久，农场发生了一场偶发的牛瘟。 -- The ranch had a *incidental* cattle plague, soon after my *coincidental* visit there. }
#{254}{}{I did not count on this; and you knew about it. Now Oliver won't be able to be pushed to an agreement, solving our disputes with minimal bloodshed. After this news, our cooperation has come to an end. Get out of my casino.}
{254}{}{我没有指望，你也知道。现在奥利弗将无法达成协议，以最少的流血解决我们的争端。听到这个消息后，我们的合作结束了。离开我的赌场。 -- I did not count on this; and you knew about it. Now Oliver won't be able to be pushed to an agreement, solving our disputes with minimal bloodshed. After this news, our cooperation has come to an end. Get out of my casino.}
#{255}{}{[Leave]}
{255}{}{[离开] -- [Leave]}
#{256}{}{Great job! With such losses, Oliver will be much more malleable. Here is the payment for your services.}
{256}{}{干得好！有了这样的损失，奥利弗将更具可塑性。这是您的服务费。 -- Great job! With such losses, Oliver will be much more malleable. Here is the payment for your services.}
#{257}{}{Thanks, boss.}
{257}{}{谢谢，老板。 -- Thanks, boss.}
#{258}{}{From now on you can forget about him and his ranch. I will speak to him personally to offer help to rebuild his business. Now negotiations depend on me.}
{258}{}{从现在起你可以忘记他和他的农场。我会亲自和他谈谈，帮助他重建生意。现在谈判全靠我了。 -- From now on you can forget about him and his ranch. I will speak to him personally to offer help to rebuild his business. Now negotiations depend on me.}
#{259}{}{So, you don't need my services?}
{259}{}{所以，你不需要我的服务？ -- So, you don't need my services?}
#{260}{}{Well, you did all that I asked for. But, there is one last business. I will not insist if you refuse, nor will I ask twice. This is my personal request... Some family drama, so to speak.}
{260}{}{好吧，我要你做的你都做了。但是，还有最后一件事。如果你拒绝，我不会坚持，我也不会要求你两次。这是我个人的要求。。。可以说是家庭剧。 -- Well, you did all that I asked for. But, there is one last business. I will not insist if you refuse, nor will I ask twice. This is my personal request... Some family drama, so to speak.}
#{261}{}{It is an honor to help you and your family.}
{261}{}{很荣幸能帮助你和你的家人。 -- It is an honor to help you and your family.}
#{262}{}{Oh, I don't interfere with domestic proceedings. I'm sorry, boss.}
{262}{}{哦，我不干涉国内诉讼。对不起，老板。 -- Oh, I don't interfere with domestic proceedings. I'm sorry, boss.}
#{263}{}{I do not blame you. All of this work must have exhausted you. Well, head to the bar and unwind yourself at my expense. I won't keep you any longer.}
{263}{}{我不怪你。所有这些工作一定把你累坏了。好吧，去酒吧放松一下，费用由我承担。我不会再留你了。 -- I do not blame you. All of this work must have exhausted you. Well, head to the bar and unwind yourself at my expense. I won't keep you any longer.}
#{264}{}{[Leave.]}
{264}{}{[离开] -- [Leave.]}
#{265}{}{My son, Huey, must conduct a family affair. The problem is that the he has always been distinguished with... Superfluous pity. He has to kill a scoundrel, and your task is to make sure that everything goes *successfully*. After that, you will tell me how it went. Now get down to the first floor; there, you will find Huey.}
{265}{}{我儿子休伊必须处理家庭事务。问题是，他一直以。。。多余的怜悯。他必须杀死一个无赖，而你的任务是确保一切顺利。在那之后，你会告诉我是怎么回事。现在到一楼去，在那里，你会找到休伊。 -- My son, Huey, must conduct a family affair. The problem is that the he has always been distinguished with... Superfluous pity. He has to kill a scoundrel, and your task is to make sure that everything goes *successfully*. After that, you will tell me how it went. Now get down to the first floor; there, you will find Huey.}
#{266}{}{I will not fail you, Mr. Bertolini.}
{266}{}{我不会让你失望的，伯托里尼先生。 -- I will not fail you, Mr. Bertolini.}
#{267}{}{And that's not everything. }
{267}{}{这不是全部。 -- And that's not everything. }
#{268}{}{In addition, all of the slaves *accidentally* triggered their shock collars. The ranch was left without any slave labor. }
{268}{}{此外，所有的奴隶*意外地*触发了他们的电击项圈。牧场没有任何奴隶劳动。 -- In addition, all of the slaves *accidentally* triggered their shock collars. The ranch was left without any slave labor. }
#{270}{}{As far as I know, you and Huey have returned from the scene. What happened there?}
{270}{}{据我所知，你和休伊已经从现场回来了。那里发生了什么？ -- As far as I know, you and Huey have returned from the scene. What happened there?}
#{271}{}{I made Huey shoot a snitch. He himself would have failed to do so.}
{271}{}{我让休伊射杀了一个告密者。他自己也不会这么做。 -- I made Huey shoot a snitch. He himself would have failed to do so.}
#{272}{}{I had to personally deal with the informer. Huey just stood aside and bellowed like a child.}
{272}{}{我不得不亲自和告密者打交道。休伊只是站在一边，像个孩子似的吼叫着。 -- I had to personally deal with the informer. Huey just stood aside and bellowed like a child.}
#{273}{}{Huey had the courage to finish the matter.}
{273}{}{休伊有勇气完成这件事。 -- Huey had the courage to finish the matter.}
#{274}{}{Huey allowed the victim to escape. I was unable to stop them.}
{274}{}{休伊允许受害者逃跑。我无法阻止他们。 -- Huey allowed the victim to escape. I was unable to stop them.}
#{275}{}{That sounds plausible. I know Huey very well - he lacks guts to do so. Strictly speaking, I knew that you have to do it, so accept my thanks along with payment.}
{275}{}{听起来似乎有道理。我很了解休伊――他没有勇气这么做。严格地说，我知道你必须这样做，所以接受我的感谢和付款。 -- That sounds plausible. I know Huey very well - he lacks guts to do so. Strictly speaking, I knew that you have to do it, so accept my thanks along with payment.}
#{276}{}{Thanks, Mr. Betrolini.}
{276}{}{谢谢，贝特洛里尼先生。 -- Thanks, Mr. Betrolini.}
#{277}{}{You're lying. I know Huey very well. He lacks the guts to do so. I had hoped that you would do the work for him, but in the end you're lying to defend him. I don't know what you expect, but the job is done, and I am obliged to pay. From now on, I don't need your services. You may leave.}
