#{310}{}{You're such a famous person in Reno. I always wanted to get to know you closer... }
{310}{}{你真是雷诺的名人。我一直想更进一步地了解你。。。 -- You're such a famous person in Reno. I always wanted to get to know you closer... }
#{311}{}{[He grins lewdly] Sometimes I get bored in this town. All of these silly girls from the streets don't even know the rules of etiquette, and there's never much to talk about with them. Are you one of them, or just giving in to temptation?}
{311}{}{[他露齿而笑]有时候我在这个镇上会觉得无聊。所有这些来自街头的傻女孩都不懂礼节，也从来没有什么可以和她们谈论的。你是他们中的一员，还是仅仅屈服于诱惑？ -- [He grins lewdly] Sometimes I get bored in this town. All of these silly girls from the streets don't even know the rules of etiquette, and there's never much to talk about with them. Are you one of them, or just giving in to temptation?}
#{312}{}{What are you saying?! Yuck! How could you! I would never lower myself to that level.}
{312}{}{你在说什么？！讨厌！你怎么能！我决不会把自己降低到那个水平。 -- What are you saying?! Yuck! How could you! I would never lower myself to that level.}
#{313}{}{Is it really so important to you on who to sleep with? Because you can afford anyone. Even several ones at the same time.}
{313}{}{和谁上床对你来说真的那么重要吗？因为你负担得起任何人。甚至同时有几个。 -- Is it really so important to you on who to sleep with? Because you can afford anyone. Even several ones at the same time.}
#{314}{}{My rose doesn't bloom for just anyone - and surely not for street rags.}
{314}{}{我的玫瑰不会为任何人绽放――当然也不会为街头的破烂而绽放。 -- My rose doesn't bloom for just anyone - and surely not for street rags.}
#{315}{}{Methinks I've started with the wrong topic. Excuse me; I need a restroom.}
{315}{}{我想我是从错误的话题开始的。对不起，我需要一个洗手间。 -- Methinks I've started with the wrong topic. Excuse me; I need a restroom.}
#{316}{}{Many have claimed the same. Some lied, while others were genuinely convinced that they themselves make their own life decisions... What do you count on - to remain innocent and undamaged in this town?}
{316}{}{许多人也声称如此。有些人撒谎，而另一些人则真心相信，他们自己做自己的人生决定。。。你指望什么――在这个镇上保持清白和完好无损？ -- Many have claimed the same. Some lied, while others were genuinely convinced that they themselves make their own life decisions... What do you count on - to remain innocent and undamaged in this town?}
#{317}{}{And why not? I'm counting on finding someone who I'll like. I have all the chances to choose, not to be chosen.}
{317}{}{为什么不呢？我指望能找到我喜欢的人。我有所有的机会去选择，而不是被选择。 -- And why not? I'm counting on finding someone who I'll like. I have all the chances to choose, not to be chosen.}
#{318}{}{Hmm. [he skeptically narrows his eyes and slowly blows cigarette smoke] A courtesan? You wield your tongue well. Are you a longtime resident in this town?}
{318}{}{嗯[他怀疑地眯起眼睛，慢慢地抽着烟]一个妓女？你的舌头挥舞得很好。你是这个镇的长期居民吗？ -- Hmm. [he skeptically narrows his eyes and slowly blows cigarette smoke] A courtesan? You wield your tongue well. Are you a longtime resident in this town?}
#{319}{}{No. Is this really important?}
{319}{}{不，这真的很重要吗？ -- No. Is this really important?}
#{320}{}{Nevermind. I just want to understand how soiled you are in this dirty world. Here in Reno, people are changing as time passes. Urban life makes them sophisticated, vile and sly.}
{320}{}{没有关系。我只想知道你在这个肮脏的世界里有多肮脏。在里诺，人们随着时间的推移而改变。城市生活使他们变得复杂、卑鄙和狡猾。 -- Nevermind. I just want to understand how soiled you are in this dirty world. Here in Reno, people are changing as time passes. Urban life makes them sophisticated, vile and sly.}
#{321}{}{Yeah. [make a bored look] I noticed.}
{321}{}{是 啊。我注意到了。 -- Yeah. [make a bored look] I noticed.}
#{322}{}{[He raises his brows] Did I bore you?}
{322}{}{我让你厌烦了吗？ -- [He raises his brows] Did I bore you?}
#{323}{}{Mr. Bertolini - you know... You're boring. VERY boring.}
{323}{}{伯托里尼先生-你知道。。。你真无聊。很无聊。 -- Mr. Bertolini - you know... You're boring. VERY boring.}
#{324}{}{Yes. You're telling the truth... Look, I'm busy right now. Put yourself in order if you want to continue this conversation. You look... Like a rural girl who spent all day digging potatoes.}
{324}{}{对。你说的是实话。。。听着，我现在很忙。如果你想继续这段对话，就把你自己整理好。你看起来。。。就像一个整天挖土豆的农村女孩。 -- Yes. You're telling the truth... Look, I'm busy right now. Put yourself in order if you want to continue this conversation. You look... Like a rural girl who spent all day digging potatoes.}
#{325}{}{What impudence! Fine, Mr. Bertolini, I'll put myself in order. I'm just not sure, if it'll be for you, or someone else.}
{325}{}{真是厚颜无耻！好吧，伯托里尼先生，我会整理好的。我只是不确定，是给你还是给别人。 -- What impudence! Fine, Mr. Bertolini, I'll put myself in order. I'm just not sure, if it'll be for you, or someone else.}
#{326}{}{Yes. You're telling the truth... [he claps his hands] I know what we'll do. We'll take a bottle of wine and retire to my office. You drink wine, right?}
{326}{}{对。你说的是实话。。。[他拍手]我知道我们要做什么。我们带瓶酒到我办公室去。你喝酒，对吧？ -- Yes. You're telling the truth... [he claps his hands] I know what we'll do. We'll take a bottle of wine and retire to my office. You drink wine, right?}
#{327}{}{I would prefer a martini, Mr. Bertolini.}
{327}{}{我想要一杯马提尼，伯托里尼先生。 -- I would prefer a martini, Mr. Bertolini.}
#{328}{}{Now I look forward to only one thing - to get out of this room.}
{328}{}{现在我只期待一件事――离开这个房间。 -- Now I look forward to only one thing - to get out of this room.}
#{329}{}{No one is holding you here.}
{329}{}{没有人把你关在这里。 -- No one is holding you here.}
#{330}{}{[He chuckles] Whatever you say, darling. Whatever you say.}
{330}{}{不管你说什么，亲爱的。不管你说什么。 -- [He chuckles] Whatever you say, darling. Whatever you say.}
#{331}{}{[Leave.]}
{331}{}{[离开] -- [Leave.]}
#{340}{}{I'm not counting on anything. I'm just too bored in this town.}
{340}{}{我什么都没指望。我在这个镇上太无聊了。 -- I'm not counting on anything. I'm just too bored in this town.}
#{341}{}{It's been ages; and during that time, I never found a worthy partner.}
